Hello! I'm adding a `url` field to my module with only `CONTENT` links. I'd like to know how I should populate the `default` value so that on the `design previewer` I can see a dropdown menu. Here is what I mean:
1. When I try to edit the default link on the previewer, I can only see the URL as text. e.g.: "buy-home" in the first screenshot
2. When I try to add a new link, I can see the dropdown menu as expected, in the second screenshot attached.
*So, how can I achieve the same for the default link?*

This is what I'm doing right now:
```{
    "name": "buttons",
    "label": "Buttons",
    "type": "group",
    "occurrence": {
      "default": 2,
      "min": 1,
      "max": 3
    },
    "children": [
      {
        "name": "link_url",
        "label": "Link Url",
        "required": false,
        "locked": false,
        "supported_types": [ "CONTENT" ],
        "type": "url",
        "default": {
          "content_id": null,
          "href": "",
          "type": "CONTENT"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "link_txt",
        "label": "Link Text",
        "type": "text",
        "default": "Title"
      }
    ],
    "default": [
      {
        "link_url": { "href": "buy-home" },
        "link_txt": "Home Purchase"
      },
      {
        "link_url": { "href": "refinance" },
        "link_txt": "Refinance"
      }
    ]
  }```
Thanks!!
